20/01/2008
ANKARA, Turkey -- About 60 bases of the Kurdistan Workers' Party (PKK) in northern Iraq were destroyed in the latest operation of the Turkish army against the militants, the Turkish General Staff said in a statement on Friday (January 18th). 
The operation, which was carried out on January 15th, was the fourth offensive against the PKK after the Turkish parliament gave a green light to the operations in mid-October. 
(RIA Novosti, Svoboda, Reuters, Press TV, Turkish Daily News, Xinhua - 18/01/08)
